gomodel:SYNGO_4001  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0030285 replaced by GO:0030672" , "Rationale: Figure 2D: Distribution of native Syt12 in subcellular fractions of adult rat brain separated by centrifugation. Similar to synaptotagmin-1 (Syt 1) and synaptobrevin/VAMP2 (Syb 2), Syt12 is enriched in synaptic vesicle fraction (crude SVs).\nFig2 E and F: Syt12 expression was reduced by ~40% in the synapsin DKO brains, which exactly corresponds to the decrease observed for other synaptic vesicle proteins. The levels of synaptic proteins that are not localized on synaptic vesicles, such as the synaptotagmin isoforms 3, 6, and 7 or NMDA-receptors, were not decreased in synapsin double knockout mice. This further specifies that Syt12 is localised in the synaptic vesicle.\nFig2 G: Immunoelectron microscopy demonstrates Syt12 immunoreactivity over the synaptic vesicle cluster in presynaptic terminals in hippocampal neurons.\nFigure 2 I and J: Immunohistochemical analysis demonstrates the colocalisation of Syt12 with presynaptic marker, synaptophysin and localises opposite to dendritic marker, MAP2.\n\nNote on Ab specificity:\nFigure 2C and H: The Syt12 labelling was specific because preincubation with the antigen greatly reduced synaptotagmin-12 immunoreactivity in brain sections as well as in the immunoelectron image.\n\nSyt12 has a transmembrane domain [19-39] and hence the term \"integral component of synaptic vesicle\" was chosen.. Experimental description: Whole rat brains, including the cerebellum and olfactory bulb, were homogenized for subcellular fractionation experiments.\nFor colocalisation studies, synaptotagmin-12 lentivirus was prepared from full-length Syt12 cDNA (aa 1-421) and was subcloned into pFUGW shuttle vector.\nAdult mouse brains (hippocampus) was used for electron microscopy experiments." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2916-7616" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4001" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
